@NODE Requirements "Requirements"

Requirements
============

An  Amiga  with  at  least 512K RAM and Kickstart 2.04 is needed.
For localization and screenmode requester you need Kickstart 2.1.
With Kickstart 3.0 some gadgets can be coloured and "shared pens"
can be used.

The program was tested on:

- Amiga  500 with Kickstart 2.04, 2.1
- Amiga 2000 with Kickstart 3.1, Picasso
- Amiga 4000

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"

Installation
============

You  should copy the catalog file for your prefered language into
LOCALE:Catalogs.  That's all.  The default language is English.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Configuration "Configuration"

Configuration
=============

The  program  has  a built in preference editor.  The preferences
file is saved in PROGDIR:.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Using "Using"

Using
=====

The program can be started from CLI and from Workbench.  4K stack
should be enough.

Normally  you  will  work with the mouse, but you also can switch
the 5 dice gadgets with the keys F1 to F5.

The active player is marked with a coloured border.

If  you  leave  the  game  the names and the cumulate results are
stored, so you can continue your game later.

